Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
fix_feedthru_assign(25.10)                          fix_feedthru_assign(25.10)

Name
       fix_feedthru_assign  -  Fixes the assign statements that are associated
       with partitions by replacing them with the specified buffer

Syntax
       fix_feedthru_assign

       [-help]

       -buffer <string>[-delete_feed]

       Fixes the assign statements that are associated with partitions by  re-
       placing them with the specified buffer. This helps to minimize the num-
       ber  of buffers that are added to the design when assign statements are
       deleted.

       The fix_feedthru_assign command enables selective replacement of assign
       statements with real buffers.

Parameters
       -buffer <string>
              Specifies the buffer to be used for replacing assign statements.

              Data_type: string, required

       -delete_feed
              Removes input-output(s) assigns from within the  partition  mod-
              ule.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each fix_feedthru_assign parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man fix_feedthru_assign

Example
       The following command replaces the assign  statements  associated  with
       partitions with the specified buffer.

       fix_feedthru_assign -buffer abc

